commit.message:
dtoverlay: Copy local fixups when necessary

If an intra fragment includes a phandle value then the local fixups
muxt be updated to include the target location, otherwise the phandle
won't get rebased when applied to the base dtb.

Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>

dtoverlay: Expose dtoverlay_merge_fragment

Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>

dtoverlay_main: Restore copyright indentation

Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>

dtoverlay/dtparam: Correctly detect last parameter

The loop parsing parameters separated by commas, perhaps from the
overlay_map file, wasn't spotting the end of the string, resulting in
strange errors such as:

    * Unknown parameter 'NO_AT_BRIDGE'

Fix it.

Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>

pinctrl/gpiolib: Mark gpiochips as "used" for LTO

GCC's Link Time Optimisation feature can cause the link-to-register
feature of gpiolib to fail - without an explicit reference to the data
it is assumed to be unused, and dropped. Add the "used" attribute to
prevent this.

See: https://github.com/raspberrypi/utils/issues/75

Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>

pinctrl: Speed up RP1 GPIO drive set

Use the atomic set/clr feature of RP1 to set the output drive on a
GPIO, which makes it much faster.

See: https://github.com/raspberrypi/utils/issues/73

Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>

raspinfo: Add sudo to dmesg

You can configure the kernel to require root to access dmesg.
Lets use sudo anyway - we already do in other places in this script

pinctrl: Add the echo (-e) option

Echo mode, enabled with the -e option, causes a 'set' operation to
display the resulting pin states without the need for a separate 'get'.

Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>

dtmerge: Fix uninitialised variable

Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>

ovmerge: Don't create 'i2c' as a label

When "Pi extras" are enabled, ovmerge creates the same I2C labels and
aliases as the firmware. The label 'i2c' is no longer added by the
firmware, so remove it from the list of additions here.

Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>

eeplib: Don't use arithmetic on void pointers

Although gcc allows arithmetic on void pointers as if they were
pointers to bytes, not all compilers do. Apply some casts to avoid
compilation errors.

Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>

dtmerge: Make i2c_arm/vc creation conditional

Use the same rules as the firmware when it comes to creating the i2c_arm
and i2c_vc symbols and aliases - only do so when there isn't already an
"i2c" alias.

Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>

overlaycheck: Apply all overlays to one platform

For each overlay, choose a platform based on the overlay compatible
string to ensure there are no unresolved symbols, etc.

Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>

pinctrl: Support older versions of glibc

reallocarray was made part of the standard glibc in 2.29, but defining
_GNU_SOURCE allows pinctrl to build on older versions.

See: https://github.com/raspberrypi/utils/issues/68
     https://forums.raspberrypi.com/viewtopic.php?t=364773

Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>

eeptools: eepdump: init type before calling eepio_atom_start

Signed-off-by: lvaro Fernndez Rojas <noltari@gmail.com>

eeptools: Fix compiler warnings

Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>

eeptools: Add to top-level CMakeLists.txt

Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>
Typo
raspinfo: Add some audio info to debug log

Add eeptools (the HAT+ EEPROM tools)

The eeptools project replaces eepromutils in the old hats repo. It
supports the HAT+ standard and old V1 HATs.

Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>
Removes old -t and -h description.

ovmerge: Avoid warning about ininitialised value

Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>

ovmerge: Improve fragment order checking

Strengthen the fragment order checking by assuming that all dormant
fragments may be merged if the right parameter is used.

Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>

vcgencmd: Clarify man page

A description of the get_throttled output in the vcgencmd man page
fails to include bit 0, which can be confusing. Add it.

Fixes: https://github.com/raspberrypi/utils/issues/53
Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>

dtmerge/dtoverlay: Pass all regression tests

Using dtoverlay to create a runtime overlay and merging that with a
base dtb, then comparing against merging the overlay directly with
the base dtb, showed some difference (and therefore errors).

Fix those errors by passing the stringlist length around, and by
correctly remembering the offset of the used value in a lookup table.

Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>

dtoverlay: intra fragments, phandles in overrides

Intra fragments (those that target other fragments in the overlay)
require special handling when applying overlays at runtime because
they have the potential to copy phandles, breaking the fixups.
Similarly for overrides that write phandle values.

Add logic to detect those cases and patch the fixups accordingly.

See: https://github.com/raspberrypi/linux/issues/5652

Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>

dtmerge: Reindent to 4-characters, no TABs

The code had a mixture of 3- and 4-character indentation.

Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>

ovmerge: Check intra fragment merge order

Ensure that intra fragments are not being applied to fragments that have
already been merged, in a way that can be used by overlaycheck.

Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>

ovmerge: Enable warnings

Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>

ovmerge: Add literal path assignment example

Signed-off-by: Phil Elwell <phil@raspberrypi.com>
